<paragraph base="F55751314" id="IFRS17_BC88"><paranum>BC88</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IFRS 17"/><data name="paranum" value="BC88"/></prolog><body><bodydiv base="IFRS2020-3">             <p id="IFRS17_P5963">IFRS 17 also allows an entity a choice of applying IFRS 17 or                 another IFRS Standard to some contracts, specifically: </p>             <ol type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value><p>applying IFRS 17 or <xref base="F59367740" href="../ifrs14/IFRS15_TOC.dita#IFRS15_TOC0001/IFRS15_TOC0001_V2" id="IFRS17_X1508">IFRS 15</xref> to some fixed-fee service contracts                         (see <xref base="F59367741" href="IFRS17_gBC95-BC97.dita#IFRS17_gBC95-BC97/IFRS17_gBC95-BC97_TI" id="IFRS17_X1509">paragraphs BC95&#x2013;BC97</xref>); and</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value><p>applying IFRS 17 or <xref href="../ifrs09/IFRS09_TOC.dita">IFRS 9</xref> to specified contracts                         such as loan contracts with death waivers (see <xref href="IFRS17_gBC94D-BC94F.dita#IFRS17_gBC94D-BC94F/IFRS17_gBC94D-BC94F_TI">paragraphs BC94D&#x2012;BC94F</xref>).</p></li></ol>         </bodydiv></body></paragraph>